              "free_text": [
                " K-400 Neutron Generator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Sample pellets (0.2 cm in thickness, 2.0 cm in",
                "diameter, around 3 g in weight, and >99.99% pure)",
                "were pressed from natural Tm2O3 powder. Each of them",
                "was sandwiched between two Nb metal foils, and the",
                "purity of the Nb foils was >99.99%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were produced with an effective",
                "deuteron beam energy of 136 keV and beam current of",
                "280 uA. The T-Mo target used in the generator had a",
                "thickness of 0.566 mg/cm2 and an active area with a",
                "diameter of 1.2 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High-purity germanium detector (ORTEC, model",
                "GEM 60P, crystal diameter: 70.1 mm, crystal length:",
                "72.3 mm, made in the United States) with a relative",
                "efficiency of around 68% and an energy resolution of",
                "1.69 keV at 1332 keV for 60Co."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Lasted about 13 h with a yield of about 2 to",
                "3E10 n/(4pi*s). The groups of samples were placed at",
                "0- or 135-deg angle relative to the beam direction",
                "and centered about the tritium-molybdenum (T-Mo)",
                "target at distances of about 4 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
